The staff were friendly, and the food was pretty good. There's a nice outdoor seating area, and they have a happy hour.

Since today is Taco Tuesday, I decided to get some tacos. I ordered 3 original tacos (2 beef & 1 chicken) which came with pico de gallo, a side order of guacamole & 2 margaritas. I placed my order, waited a short time (surprising because it was busy) and took my food home (less than 10 mins away). When I got home, all of the tacos were dumped with a lot of shredded lettuce and a little bit of meat. None of the meat was seasoned and my hard tacos were soggy af! The margaritas were watered down (I’ve had the margaritas before and it was nothing like this). The only good thing was the salsa, chips and guacamole. I was so disappointed in my visit to Lime today smh.

I love the service I received the waiter was very nice & polite as well as the cashier she helped me out to decide what was best and vegetarian to order for my husband the slushy drinks are the best I highly recommend you to try one happy house starts from 4 to 6pm.

Lime used to be an awesome place for my girlfriend and I to have some Margaritas and enjoy some good food. Since we are at-risk, we can no longer Dine-in to Lime and are forced to resort to take-out. The order we made today will unfortunately be our last. For the last 3 times we've ordered from here, they simply refuse to give us ANY salsa... every dish served here comes with tortilla chips which requires said salsa, unless a bland chip is something you'd like to eat a lot of. It's frustrating that the plethora of FREE salsas offered at this place, a staple of the joint, never makes it to our home. Adding to insult, the steak in the quesadillas were chewy and disgusting. No more Lime for us unfortunately, the quality and customer care has gone to the gutter.

The cashier was extremely rude, she didn’t acknowledge me when I walked in. And when I went to order she kept asking me to repeat myself and would sigh loudly after everything I said as if I was bothering her by ordering. I ended up walking out because of her. I understand it’s harder to hear through a mask but I was speaking up and enunciating, I’ve never had problems at any other restaurant when using a mask. She clearly didn’t want me to be there or order so I won’t be back.

Love lime, was very happy they opened a location here. It's very reasnobly priced and with nice portions. We had two super tacos and a nacho. The nacho was ok. Good not great. But the tacos were ridiculous. They put so much food (mostly sour cream and lettuce) on the smallest tortilla possible that it couldn't even be picked up. Had to eat it with a knife and fork and it got messy real fast. Honestly, why would you make a taco like that to begin with?  Are you even a chef? They either don't know or don't care that tacos are a hand-held food. Probably won't order from them again. Especially when La Taqueria is so close by. I mean if you're going to throw down in the Mission, you better come correct.

it's not the same old LIME. The frozen margarita is 2 sweet. They should of kept it the way it was two flavors only. The sauces are no longer available.  I could go on but I do not want to bash them that bad. They do need improvement.

My first time at this lime, the cashier was very friendly and explained the menu items we had questions on. There was some mistake on how the order was taken it seemed and Grant, the owner or manager came by to clarify. Not only did he clarify he made sure to correct a very minor mistake, and he did it with pleasure. The cashier also came by to check on us and offered extra chips for the kids. The food at Lime is always pretty consistently good,but the experience at this Lime location in particular was above expectations.  I had the fried fish tacos which were piping hot, delicious, chips and queso with ground beef, and nachos with steak. All very fresh, very good.
